The SAPPHIRE Format is known in-universe as the â€œZetetic Bulletinâ€.[[footnote]]Fun fact! The Flat Earth Society was originally known as the Universal Zetetic Society. [[/footnote]] For an example of the format in action, see:

* **[[[zetetic-bulletin-wu-xing-iris|The Myth of the Wu Xing Iris]]]** by **[[*user Uncle Nicolini]]**.

Open the format by pasting the following div //before// or //after// the rating module:[[footnote]] If you ask me, it looks cleaner //before//. [[/footnote]]

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@[[div class="sapphire-block"]]@@
[[/div]]

The SAPPHIRE Format is a mock essay or dissertation. Each paragraph is **indented**[[footnote]] Except for the introductory paragraph. [[/footnote]] and the entire format's text is **justified**. Both these properties are pre-baked into the theme's CSS.

Next, indicate the format's title and in-universe author's name (not your own):

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@++* Title@@
@@+++* By Name@@
[[/div]]

Then, a section heading, which is often used several times throughout the format:

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@[[div class="lite-heading"]]@@
@@----@@
@@++++ SECTION HEADING@@
@@----@@
@@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]

For quoted passages:

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@[[div class="excerpt"]]@@
Text here.
@@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]

Example:

[[div class="excerpt"]]
Ignorance more frequently begets confidence than does knowledge: it is those who know little, and not those who know much, who so positively assert that this or that problem will never be solved by science.[((bibcite darwin))]
[[/div]]

If your article has any footnotes or bibliographic citations, place their respective blocks at the end of all inner elements. If you're unsure about how to set up a bibliography, [*https://www.wikidot.com/doc-wiki-syntax:bibliography Wikidot provides a short explanation]. Any bibliography section should come after the footnotes:

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@~~~~@@
@@[[footnoteblock]]@@
[[/div]]

Finally, close the format. Include SAPPHIRE's watchword for extra points:

[[div class="code slim"]]
@@----@@
@@+++* When in doubt, doubt.@@
@@[[/div]]@@
[[/div]]

And you're done!
----
